headline: Liver Drug Approval and Pipeline Data Could Be a Game Changer for Gilead Sciences (GILD)
summary: In recent weeks, Gilead Sciences announced Health Canada's conditional approval of LYVDELZI (seladelpar) for primary biliary cholangitis, and presented new positive clinical data across its liver disease and oncology pipeline at major global conferences. This wave of regulatory and clinical milestones underscores Gilead's momentum in diversifying beyond its HIV franchise with late-stage therapies addressing major unmet needs.
